Description: # Slydes
        Why not show your presentations with Python?
        
        ### Create a presentation
        `$ cat presentation.py`
        
        ```python
        from slydes import Presentation, Template
        
        
        talk = Presentation()
        template = Template()
        
        
        @talk.add_slide
        def first_slide():
            title = 'This is the title!'
            msg = '''
            Hello world!
            My name is PySlides!
            '''
            return template.default(title, msg)
            
        
        @talk.add_slide
        def second_slide():
            title = 'The second slide!'
            msg = '''
            * Bullet points!
            * why
            * not?
            '''
            return template.default(title, msg)
        
        
        @talk.add_slide
        def third_slide():
            title = 'The last slide!'
            msg = 'Bye world!'
            return template.default(title, msg)
        ```
        
        
        ### Run it!
        `$ ipython`
        ```bash
        from presentation import talk
        
        talk.next()
        --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
        #                                                                              #
        #                                                                              #
        #      This is the title!                                                      #
